s, which became important in the mid\nTertiary, from around . The grasses, as well as many other groups, evolved new\nmechanisms of metabolism to survive the low and warm, dry conditions of the\ntropics over the last .\n","linknr":1891,"url":"Evolution_of_leaves","recorded":1362482869,"links":79,"instances":["biology","medical","evolution","biology"],"pdf":["http://www.humboldt.edu/biosci/docs/faculty/TomescuRothwell2006.pdf","http://www.humboldt.edu/biosci/docs/faculty/TomescuRothwell2006.pdf","http://geology.geoscienceworld.org/cgi/reprint/35/5/399.pdf","http://geology.geoscienceworld.org/cgi/reprint/35/5/399.pdf","http://www.journals.royalsoc.ac.uk/index/YTH8204514044972.pdf","http://www.journals.royalsoc.ac.uk/index/YTH8204514044972.pdf"],"categories":["Plants","Paleobotany","Evolution by taxon"],"headings":["Colonization of land{{anchor|land}}","Evolution of life cycles{{anchor|phases}}{{anchor|life cycles}}","Evolution of morphology","Evolution of photosynthetic pathways","Evolution of secondary metabolism","Mechanisms and players in evolution of plant form","See also","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c0/Trilete_spores.png/220px-Trilete_spores.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/5/7/c/57cec4137b614c87cb4e24a3d003a3e0.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/ba/Devonianscene-green.jpg/220px-Devonianscene-green.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e1/Angiosperm_life_cycle_diagram.svg/220px-Angiosperm_life_cycle_diagram.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/96/Banded_tube.jpg/220px-Banded_tube.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2b/Illustration_Isoetes_